<DIV1 TYPE="title page">
<PB REF="016169_0002_0F9BD86F1AFFAEA0">
<P>AN ANNIVERSARY SERMON, PREACHED AT PLYMOUTH, DECEMBER 22d, 1777. IN GRATEFUL MEMORY OF THE FIRST LANDING OF OUR PIOUS NEW-ENGLAND ANCESTERS IN THAT PLACE, A. D. 1620.</P>
<P>BY SAMUEL WEST, A. M. Pastor of the CHURCH in DARTMOUTH.</P>
<Q>The secret of the Lord is with them that fear him; and he will shew them his covenant.<BIBL><HI>The Psalmist David.</HI></BIBL></Q>
<Q>Surely the Lord God will do nothing, but he revealeth his secret unto his servants the prophets.<BIBL><HI>Prophet Amos.</HI></BIBL></Q>
<Q>Thus saith the Lord, the holy one of Israel, and his Maker, ask me things to come concerning my sons, and concerning the work of my hands command ye me. <BIBL><HI>Isaiah</HI> 45, 11.</BIBL></Q>
<Q>Many shall run to and fro, and knowledge shall be increased.<BIBL><HI>Daniel</HI> 12, 4.</BIBL></Q>
<P>BOSTON: PRINTED, BY DRAPER and FOLSOM, AT THEIR <HI>Printing-Office,</HI> AT THE CORNER OF <HI>Winter-Street.</HI> M,DCC,LXXVIII.</P>
